# Rust Core (Implementation)

- **Small diffs:** Prefer incremental changes. One logical change per edit session; avoid bundling unrelated fixes.
- **No scope creep:** Implement only what the task or design log specifies. Do not add new features or refactors unless explicitly asked.
- **Dependencies:** Do not add new dependencies unless the user or design log explicitly requests them.
- **Avoid unwrap/expect in production paths:** Use proper error handling (`Result`, `?`, or `match`) for user-facing or library code. `unwrap`/`expect` are acceptable in tests, examples, or clearly unreachable paths; document why if used.
- **Verification:** After edits, run (from project root or workspace root):
  - `cargo fmt --all -- --check` (fix with `cargo fmt --all` if needed)
  - `cargo clippy --fix --allow-dirty --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`
  - `cargo test --all-features`
  Optionally: `cargo audit`, `cargo check --all-targets --all-features`. Fix any failures before considering the task done.
